ht into our own political life, Yack makes a valuable contribution to contemporary discourse and debate. His work will excite interest among a wide range of social, moral, and political theorists.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aCommunities. 0aJustice. 0aSocial conflict. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520913509?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520913509423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520913509/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles